  <name value="Combat Zone Work segment"/>
  <withdrawn value="false"/>
  <abbreviation value="OH4"/>
  <description>
    <status value="additional"/>
    <div>
      <description>
        <status value="additional"/>
        <div>
          <p>The OH4 segment contains the date range an individual has worked in what is considered a combat or hazardous duty zone; both civilian and military.</p>
          <p>The intent is for the segment to be allowed to repeat within a message definition to enable a combat zone history for the patient.</p>
          <p>Examples:</p>
          <p>A person/ may have worked in a combat zone for 2 years, followed by 3 years where there was no combat zone work, returning to combat zone work for another 2 years. This would be reflected as two Combat work segments documenting the date ranges for the 2 periods when the combat zone work occurred.</p>
          <p>HL7 Attribute Table – OH4 – Combat Zone Work</p>
        </div>
      </description>
    </div>
  </description>
